# ========================================
TC-AMS-DELETE-01

SUMMARY
AMS R1 - Successfully Delete a Parcel as AMS Response

DESCRIPTION
Verifies the complete delete parcel journey for an Advisor/Agent or Farmer responding to an AMS Round 1 Red finding. The test covers the full flow from login through to selecting a parcel for deletion via the bin symbol in the side drawer. It verifies the delete confirmation popup message inside the side drawer, the warning message about impact on other area based scheme payments, saving the deletion, the strikethrough styling on the deleted parcel row, the blank status, the green toast confirmation, and the yellow warning banner that appears at the top of the AMS response screen after deletion. No changes from last year functionality - test only.

STEPS

Action	Data	Expected Result
If Agent: Log in to BISS with agent credentials and OTP. If Farmer: Log in with farmer credentials and OTP	Agent username and password from INET query. OTP/PIN	Successfully authenticated and landed on BISS Home page
If Agent: Navigate to Agent Tools and select AMS then select the client herd. If Farmer: Navigate to Farmer Dashboard directly	Herd number from VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD query where scheme_year=2026 and expired=0	Farmer Dashboard displayed with AMS Findings panel visible
Click Respond to Findings button on the AMS Findings panel		AMS Respond to Findings screen displayed
Verify the parcels listed in the findings table		Only Round 1 Red parcels are displayed in the list
Verify the AMS findings column content		AMS findings column is populated with Artificial Surface for the relevant parcels
Verify the red symbol on each parcel row		Each parcel with a pending response shows a red symbol indicating response required
Verify the Action column on each parcel row		A View Map icon is present at the end of each parcel row
Click on a Red parcel row to open the side drawer	Parcel number from vwbs_error_land query where eor_year=2026 and ers_abbrev=A and ety_code=2028	Side drawer opens for the selected parcel
Verify the delete option is visible in the side drawer		Bin symbol/delete option is visible in the side drawer
Click the delete bin symbol		Delete confirmation popup appears inside the side drawer
Verify the delete confirmation popup message		Message reads: You have requested to delete this parcel from your BISS application. This may affect payment on other Area based schemes. Please undo if this was done in error
Confirm the deletion - do not cancel		Delete confirmed
Click Save Changes		Green toast message displayed: You have successfully marked parcel X for deletion
Verify the parcel row styling after deletion		Strikethrough is applied to the deleted parcel row to indicate it is deleted
Verify the status of the deleted parcel		Status of the parcel row is blank
Verify the yellow warning banner at the top of the AMS response screen		Yellow warning message displayed: You have decided to delete a parcel. This may affect your payments

# ========================================
TC-AMS-DELETE-02

SUMMARY
AMS R1 - Successfully Undo the Delete of a Parcel

DESCRIPTION
Verifies that a previously deleted parcel can be recovered via the Undo/Recover option in the AMS Respond to Findings screen. The test covers selecting the strikethrough parcel row, pressing Recover, verifying the yellow warning banner disappears, confirming the parcel reverts to its original values with no response selected, saving changes, and confirming the strikethrough is removed from the parcel row. No changes from last year functionality - test only.

STEPS

Action	Data	Expected Result
If Agent: Log in to BISS with agent credentials and OTP. If Farmer: Log in with farmer credentials and OTP	Same herd and agent login as TC-AMS-DELETE-01	Successfully authenticated and landed on BISS Home page
If Agent: Navigate to Agent Tools and select AMS then select the client herd. If Farmer: Navigate to Farmer Dashboard directly	Same herd as TC-AMS-DELETE-01	Farmer Dashboard displayed with AMS Findings panel visible
Click Respond to Findings button on the AMS Findings panel		AMS Respond to Findings screen displayed
Verify the yellow warning banner is present at top of screen		Yellow warning message visible: You have decided to delete a parcel. This may affect your payments
Locate the parcel row that has a strikethrough indicating it is marked for deletion	Same parcel as TC-AMS-DELETE-01	Parcel row with strikethrough visible in the list
Verify the Recover option is visible on the deleted parcel row		Recover option is displayed on the strikethrough parcel row
Click Recover on the deleted parcel row		Side drawer opens for the parcel
Verify the yellow warning banner is now gone		Yellow warning message You have decided to delete a parcel. This may affect your payments is no longer displayed
Verify the parcel values in the side drawer		Parcel shows original values with no response selected
Click Save Changes		Changes saved successfully
Verify the parcel row after saving		Strikethrough is removed from the parcel row - parcel restored to original state

# ========================================
TC-AMS-DELETE-03

SUMMARY
AMS R1 - Change Response from Accept to Reject After Saving (Pre-Submit)

DESCRIPTION
Verifies that a user who has previously accepted an AMS finding on a parcel and drawn the map can go back and change their response from Accept to Reject before submitting. The test covers reopening the side drawer for the accepted parcel, selecting Reject, choosing a reject reason, saving, and verifying that a call to LPIS occurs to delete any map that was previously drawn as part of the Accept response. This is a pre-submit change of mind scenario. No changes from last year functionality - test only.

STEPS

Action	Data	Expected Result
If Agent: Log in to BISS with agent credentials and OTP. If Farmer: Log in with farmer credentials and OTP	Same herd and agent login as TC-AMS-DELETE-01	Successfully authenticated and landed on BISS Home page
If Agent: Navigate to Agent Tools and select AMS then select the client herd. If Farmer: Navigate to Farmer Dashboard directly	Same herd as TC-AMS-DELETE-01	Farmer Dashboard displayed with AMS Findings panel visible
Click Respond to Findings button on the AMS Findings panel		AMS Respond to Findings screen displayed
Verify the parcel that was previously accepted is visible in the list	Parcel X that was accepted and had a map drawn	Parcel X is visible in the findings list showing accepted response
Click on parcel X to open the side drawer		Side drawer opens for parcel X
Verify the current response is Accept in the side drawer		Accept is shown as the current selected response for this parcel
Select Reject		Reject option selected - overriding the previous Accept response
Verify the reject reason prompt		Message displayed: Give a reason why you reject Area Monitoring findings?
Select a reject reason from the list - for example Crop is as claimed		Reject reason selected
Click Save Changes		Changes saved - call to LPIS occurs to delete any map previously drawn for the Accept response
Verify the LPIS map drawn during Accept response is deleted		Map drawn during Accept response is removed as a result of changing to Reject

# ========================================
TC-AMS-DELETE-04

SUMMARY
AMS R1 - Uncheck Request Change of EH Reverts Claimed Area to Original Value

DESCRIPTION
Verifies that when a user has previously accepted an AMS finding, changed the claimed area, and checked the Request Change of EH checkbox before saving - if they subsequently return to that parcel and uncheck the Request Change of EH checkbox, the claimed area is automatically reverted to its original value. This is a change of mind scenario for EH box behaviour. No changes from last year functionality - test only.

